episodes.title: Waiting for Dutch
episodes.plot: In a small Minnesota town, a shooting at a diner disrupts the lives of a state officer, a married couple, and a North Dakota crime syndicate.

episodes.title: Before the Law
episodes.plot: The Gerhardts receive a surprising offer, while two unlikely murderers do their best to clean up their mess.

episodes.title: The Myth of Sisyphus
episodes.plot: The Gerhardts' search for Rye intensifies, Lou takes a trip to Fargo, and Peggy overhears a new theory about the Waffle Hut shooter.

episodes.title: Fear and Trembling
episodes.plot: The Gerhardts respond to Kansas City's proposal, while Hanzee finds a new lead in Rye's disappearance. Lou questions Ed and Peggy.

episodes.title: The Gift of the Magi
episodes.plot: Floyd takes action and Charlie tries to prove himself; Peggy and Ed disagree about what to do next; Lou finds himself sidelined during Ronald Reagan's campaign tour.

episodes.title: Rhinoceros
episodes.plot: With Ed and Charlie in custody, the Gerhardts arrive at the police station, forcing Lou and Hank to try and prevent any more bloodshed.

episodes.title: Did You Do This? No, You Did It!
episodes.plot: The police bring in Floyd for questioning, in an attempt to make her talk. Bear goes on a ride with Simone. Karl keeps an eye on Lou's family.

episodes.title: Loplop
episodes.plot: Ed and Peggy hold Dodd hostage in a secluded cabin and try to strike up a deal with the Gerhardts, while Hanzee attempts to hunt them down.

episodes.title: The Castle
episodes.plot: In an attempt to stop the Kansas City mob, the police decide to use Ed and Peggy as bait. Hanzee betrays the Gerhardts and takes revenge.

episodes.title: Palindrome
episodes.plot: In the events following the motel massacre, Hanzee goes after Ed and Peggy.
